   <div class="wrapper focus"> 
    <div class="row"> 
     <h1>Finance</h1> 
     <div class="module sub2Nav"> 
      <div class="body"> 
       <ul> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/Faculty1/">Faculty</a> </li> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/Publications/">Publications</a> </li> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/Seminar-Series/">Seminar Series</a> </li> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/Research/">Research</a> </li> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/job-market-candidates/">Job Market Candidates</a> </li> 
        <li style="" class=""> <a href="/research/research-departments/Finance/vacancies/">Vacancies</a> </li> 
       </ul> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="wrapper"> 
    <div class="row"> 
     <div class="content width9"> 
      <div class="module article first"> 
       <div class="head"> 
       </div> 
       <div class="ingress"> 
        <p> <span>The Department of Finance has a strong international orientation, with faculty from leading schools in finance and economics. Our research is published in top journals and covers all areas of finance.</span> </p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="body"> 
        <div> 
         <p><img src="/InstitutterFiles/Finans/Pictures/Gruppebilde%20bro.jpg" alt="" width="945" height="363"></p> 
         <ul> 
          <li><strong>The department is ranked 10th in Europe, and 2nd in the Nordic countries, based on top-finance publications 2005-2014 (U of Texas Dallas rankings)</strong></li> 
          <li><strong>NEWS!</strong>&nbsp;We will be hosting the <a href="http://www2.bi.no/biccg/" target="_blank">BI Conference on Corporate Governance</a> on May 29, 2014. Eight leading scholars will present a recent working paper.</li> 
          <li><strong>NEWS!</strong><a href="http://www.efa-online.org/r/default.asp?iID=IMDIF" target="_blank">&nbsp;EFA 2016</a> will be hosted by BI.&nbsp;<br>The annual meeting of the European Finance Association is the biggest and most important gathering of finance scholars in Europe. BI hosted the event last time in 1996.&nbsp;</li> 
          <li><strong>Next seminar:</strong>&nbsp; 
           <ul> 
            <li>Job-talks in January 2015.</li> 
            <li>Updates coming soon.</li> 
           </ul> </li> 
          <li><strong>Recent paper accepts:</strong> 
           <ul> 
            <li><a href="http://home.bi.no/richard.priestley/research/JFQA_october_2014.pdf" target="_blank">Labor Income, Relative Wealth Concerns, and the Cross-Section of Stock Returns</a><span>, by&nbsp;Juan-Pedro Gomez, Richard Priestley, Fernando Zapatero. Forthcoming in&nbsp;</span><em>Journal of Financial and Quantitative Analysis.</em></li> 
            <li><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.jmoneco.2014.09.001" target="_blank">The scapegoat theory of exchange rates: the first tests</a>, by Marcel&nbsp;Fratzscher, Dagfinn Rime, Lucio Sarno, and Gabriele Zinna. Forthcoming <em>Journal of Monetary Economics</em>.</li> 
            <li><a href="http://home.bi.no/oyvind.bohren/work/int-ref/23_Independence_Forthcoming_EFM_2014.pdf" target="_blank">Mandatory gender balance and board independence</a>, by Øyvind Bøhren and Siv Staubo. Forthcoming <em>European Financial Management</em>.</li> 
            <li><a href="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=1344407" target="_blank">Liquidity and Shareholder Activism</a>, by Øyvind Norli, Charlotte Ostergaard, Ibolya Schindele. Forthcoming in <em>Review of Financial Studies</em>.</li> 
            <li><a href="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=1955507" target="_blank">Finance and Employment: Evidence from US Banking Deregulation</a>, by Hamid Boustanifar. Forthcoming in&nbsp;<em>Journal of Banking and Finance</em></li> 
           </ul> </li> 
          <li><strong>Workshops:</strong><br> 
           <ul> 
            <li><span>Recent:&nbsp;Young Scholars Nordic Finance Workshop.&nbsp;</span><a href="/InstitutterFiles/Finans/Program_6.pdf">Program</a><span>&nbsp;(Nov 27-28, 2014)</span></li> 
            <li>Recent:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bi.edu/research/research-centres/Centre-for-Corporate-Governance-Research/conferences/conference1/" target="_blank">15th Workshop on Corporate Governance and Investment</a>&nbsp;(Oct 3-4, 2014).</li> 
           </ul> </li> 
          <li><strong>New hire:&nbsp;</strong><a href="http://faculty.london.edu/vgala/" target="_blank">Vito Gala</a>&nbsp;from London Business School.</li> 
         </ul> 
        </div> 
        <div class="foot"> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
